{
  "text": "Based on the consensus obtained the authors call for a concerted call for action to address difficulties with under recognition of delirium (Table 1 ). In particular, they advocate more strategic education at individual and organisational levels which should be undertaken in an integrated manner. Educational approaches, targeted at all healthcare professionals wherever possible, should focus on promoting awareness of delirium and clearer training in delirium prevention and treatment. As a first step we have developed an on-line freely accessible video of patient experience which can be used to aid effective educational approaches a . An on-line freely accessible delirium e-learning tool (in Dutch) is also available b , which increases access for learners, integrates knowledge and skill development (e.g. use of screening instruments such as Confusion Assessment Method (CAM [CITATION_1] and CAM-ICU [CITATION_2] ) or Delirium Observation Screening Scale (DOSS [CITATION_3] )) and promotes active, problem-based learning.",
